## Project scaffolding (frontend + backend)

Below is a clean scaffold and the exact commands to set it up on macOS/zsh. Note: the duplicate "routes" entry in the original list is consolidated to a single `routes` folder.

---

### Frontend (Vite)

- Create a Vite app (you can choose the template interactively):

```sh
npm create vite@latest frontend
cd frontend
npm install
# Start dev server
npm run dev
```

---

### Backend (Node.js)

Desired structure:

```
backend/
    src/
        controllers/
        db/
        middlewares/
        models/
        routes/
        utils/
    .env
    .gitignore
    app.js
    constants.js
```

Create the folders/files from the workspace root:

```sh
# Create directories
mkdir -p backend/src/{controllers,db,middlewares,models,routes,utils}

# Touch base files (edit them later as needed)
touch backend/.env \
            backend/.gitignore \
            backend/app.js \
            backend/constants.js
```

Optional: initialize a backend package.json and install common packages

```sh
cd backend
npm init -y

# Example: express + dotenv + nodemon (adjust as needed)
npm i express
npm i dotenv
npm i cors
npm i mongoose
npm i jsonwebtoken
npm i bcryptj
npm i bcryptjs
npm install cookie-parser


npm i -D nodemon

# Add a dev script (optional)
# In package.json -> scripts: { "dev": "nodemon app.js" }
    